{"key":"post-10649950","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10649950</id>\n<content>I count a quart/liter jar of spawn as 1 quart.&amp;nbsp; Of course it's less than a full quart or liter of actual grain, but it's what fits in the jar and that's what counts.&amp;nbsp; When I make bulk substrates, I always just eyeball the measurements anyway, so it's all good.&amp;nbsp; Don't worry about getting percentages exact.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As you go up in the quantities of scale, there's even more fudge room.&amp;nbsp; When I'm mixing bulk substrates, I shovel manure or sawdust, etc., from my wheelbarrow to a cement mixer, spray the hose on it until it looks right, toss in a shovel or two of gypsum and rice bran and call it good after the mixer spins for a minute or so.&amp;nbsp; Nothing gets an exact measure.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10650012</next>\n<prev>10649924</prev>\n<first>10649817</first>\n<last>10650030</last>\n<when>1247196697</when>\n<utime>07/10/09 06:31 AM</utime>\n</post>"}